The paper discusses the application of the knowledge base (KB) paradigm to interactive configuration problems, which involves searching for a configuration of interrelated objects under constraints with the assistance of a system. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic in computer science (cs.LO), software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
